text:
On page http://jakarta.apache.org/jmeter/usermanual/functions.html

"Built-in functions are written in the same manner, but by convention, the names
of built-in parameters begin with "__" to avoid conflict with user value names"

Should read 

"Built-in functions are written in the same manner, but by convention, the names
of built-in functions begin with "__" to avoid conflict with user value names"
